column5: Hi All, will have a few hours tomorrow and thinking of going to scugog but wanted to see if it has had a day walleye bite over the last 3-4 days?  Any feedback would be great.
I know your asking about   '' Walleye ''   but we hit a Pike lake today that is loaded with larger size Pike and the bite was Dead as in Dead....  Maybe because of the New Moon today ....
I caught 5 this weekend, but that was a "sundown bite"
4 in total, all from shore , around 9-9:30 pm
8am to 6pm...rippin weeds for 6 eyes. Two were working on 4lbs....very good fish for the area in my experience.  There are no pike in Scugog that I know of, but lots of Muskie.  RR
